The forged papers were printed with a regular inkjet printer.
Of course, the new owners did not get it for free: Every migrant who hoped to save himself the tests paid seven thousand rubles for the document.
This is more than twice the cost of the official test: it costs a migrant worker three thousand rubles.
The most important immediate task is to protect the system from corruption, so that certificates cannot be bought easily, both officials and civil rights groups agree.
For the time being, the authorities can only promise that guest workers who fail the test the first time will be given time for a basic language course.
In addition, newcomers without language skills are offered jobs in areas where active communication with people is not necessary.
