The number of new HIV infections has been declining since 2007.
In 2011, there were about 2,700 cases.
This is about a tenth less than the year before.
What are the symptoms of an STD?
Infectious diseases can cause genital ulcers, urinary problems, discharge, lower abdominal pain, and blisters or warts.
However, they often do not cause pain or other symptoms and therefore go unnoticed.
How can you protect yourself?
Condoms can reduce the risk of infection, but they do not provide 100 percent protection.
Because some sexually transmitted diseases can also be transmitted through smear infections and close physical contact.
Therefore, experts recommend regular check-ups, especially for those who frequently change sex partners.
Early diagnosis can cure most STIs and prevent their later effects.
